Business Brief -- Adobe Resources Corp.:
   Santa Fe Energy Resources'
   Bid Is Opposed in Lawsuit
Santa Fe, a Houston oil and gas exploration company,
agreed in December to buy Adobe in a stock swap valued at
about $500 million. Also, Adobe's 9.2% convertible preferred
shares and its 12% preferred would be swapped for
combinations of Santa Fe common and preferred.
   In composite trading on the New York Stock Exchange
Friday, Adobe common closed at $5 a share, unchanged. Santa
Fe closed at $8.25, up 12.5 cents.